  "examples": [
    {
      "name": "dashboard api",
      "description": "Page with API request assertions, JSON Schema validation on responses, interactive scenarios with wait_for_request",
      "yaml": "version: \"1.0\"\nname: \"Dashboard with API Calls\"\ndescription: \"Dashboard page that loads data from multiple API endpoints\"\n\npages:\n  - id: dashboard\n    path: /dashboard\n    title: \"Dashboard\"\n\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"[data-testid=welcome-banner]\"\n        description: \"Welcome banner is displayed\"\n      - type: text_contains\n        selector: \".stats-panel\"\n        text: \"Total Users\"\n        description: \"Stats panel shows user count label\"\n      - type: element_count\n        selector: \".stat-card\"\n        min: 3\n        description: \"At least 3 stat cards are rendered\"\n      - type: screenshot_region\n        selector: \".main-content\"\n        description: \"Main content area renders correctly\"\n\n    expected_requests:\n      - method: GET\n        url_pattern: \"/api/dashboard/stats\"\n        description: \"Fetches dashboard statistics\"\n        response:\n          status: 200\n          content_type: \"application/json\"\n          body_schema:\n            type: object\n            required:\n              - totalUsers\n              - activeUsers\n              - revenue\n            properties:\n              totalUsers:\n                type: number\n              activeUsers:\n                type: number\n              revenue:\n                type: number\n\n      - method: GET\n        url_pattern: \"/api/dashboard/recent-activity\"\n        description: \"Fetches recent activity feed\"\n        response:\n          status: 200\n          content_type: \"application/json\"\n          body_schema:\n            type: object\n            required:\n              - items\n            properties:\n              items:\n                type: array\n                items:\n                  type: object\n                  required:\n                    - id\n                    - type\n                    - timestamp\n\n      - method: GET\n        url_pattern: \"/api/notifications\"\n        description: \"Fetches user notifications\"\n        response:\n          status: 200\n\n    console_expectations:\n      - level: error\n        count: 0\n\n    scenarios:\n      - id: filter-by-date\n        description: \"User filters dashboard data by date range\"\n        steps:\n          - action: click\n            selector: \".date-picker-trigger\"\n            description: \"Open date picker\"\n          - action: fill\n            selector: \"#start-date\"\n            value: \"2024-01-01\"\n          - action: fill\n            selector: \"#end-date\"\n            value: \"2024-12-31\"\n          - action: click\n            selector: \".apply-filter\"\n            description: \"Apply the date filter\"\n          - action: wait_for_request\n            url_pattern: \"/api/dashboard/stats?from=*\"\n            description: \"Stats reload with date filter\"\n          - action: assert_visible\n            selector: \".results-updated\"\n            description: \"Results update indicator appears\"\n\n      - id: export-data\n        description: \"User exports dashboard data as CSV\"\n        steps:\n          - action: click\n            selector: \"[data-testid=export-button]\"\n            description: \"Click export button\"\n          - action: click\n            selector: \"[data-testid=export-csv]\"\n            description: \"Select CSV format\"\n          - action: wait_for_request\n            url_pattern: \"/api/dashboard/export*\"\n            method: GET\n            description: \"Export endpoint is called\"\n\nvariables:\n  base_url: \"${TARGET_BASE_URL}\"\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "login page",
      "description": "Simple single-page spec with form interactions, scenarios (success + error paths), and template variables",
      "yaml": "version: \"1.0\"\nname: \"Login Page Spec\"\ndescription: \"Simple login page with form submission and redirect\"\n\npages:\n  - id: login\n    path: /login\n    title: \"Login\"\n\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"form\"\n        description: \"Login form is present\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"#email\"\n        description: \"Email input field exists\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"#password\"\n        description: \"Password input field exists\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"button[type=submit]\"\n        description: \"Submit button exists\"\n      - type: text_contains\n        selector: \"button[type=submit]\"\n        text: \"Log In\"\n        description: \"Submit button says Log In\"\n\n    console_expectations:\n      - level: error\n        count: 0\n\n    scenarios:\n      - id: successful-login\n        description: \"User logs in with valid credentials\"\n        steps:\n          - action: fill\n            selector: \"#email\"\n            value: \"{{test_user.email}}\"\n          - action: fill\n            selector: \"#password\"\n            value: \"{{test_user.password}}\"\n          - action: click\n            selector: \"button[type=submit]\"\n          - action: wait_for_navigation\n            url_pattern: \"/dashboard\"\n            description: \"Redirects to dashboard after login\"\n\n      - id: failed-login\n        description: \"User sees error with invalid credentials\"\n        steps:\n          - action: fill\n            selector: \"#email\"\n            value: \"wrong@example.com\"\n          - action: fill\n            selector: \"#password\"\n            value: \"badpassword\"\n          - action: click\n            selector: \"button[type=submit]\"\n          - action: assert_visible\n            selector: \".error-message\"\n            description: \"Error message is displayed\"\n\nvariables:\n  base_url: \"${TARGET_BASE_URL}\"\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "multi page flow",
      "description": "Multi-page e-commerce flow with setup/teardown hooks, navigation steps, and cross-page assertions",
      "yaml": "version: \"1.0\"\nname: \"E-Commerce Checkout Flow\"\ndescription: \"Multi-page flow from product browsing to order confirmation\"\n\npages:\n  - id: product-list\n    path: /products\n    title: \"Products\"\n\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \".product-grid\"\n        description: \"Product grid is displayed\"\n      - type: element_count\n        selector: \".product-card\"\n        min: 1\n        description: \"At least one product is listed\"\n\n    expected_requests:\n      - method: GET\n        url_pattern: \"/api/products\"\n        response:\n          status: 200\n          body_schema:\n            type: object\n            required:\n              - products\n            properties:\n              products:\n                type: array\n                minItems: 1\n\n  - id: cart\n    path: /cart\n    title: \"Shopping Cart\"\n\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \".cart-items\"\n        description: \"Cart items container exists\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \".cart-total\"\n        description: \"Cart total is displayed\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"[data-testid=checkout-button]\"\n        description: \"Checkout button exists\"\n\n    expected_requests:\n      - method: GET\n        url_pattern: \"/api/cart\"\n        response:\n          status: 200\n          body_schema:\n            type: object\n            required:\n              - items\n              - total\n\n  - id: checkout\n    path: /checkout\n    title: \"Checkout\"\n\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"form.checkout-form\"\n        description: \"Checkout form exists\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"#card-number\"\n        description: \"Card number input exists\"\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \".order-summary\"\n        description: \"Order summary is shown\"\n\n  - id: confirmation\n    path: /order/confirmation\n    title: \"Order Confirmation\"\n\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \".confirmation-message\"\n        description: \"Confirmation message is shown\"\n      - type: text_matches\n        selector: \".order-number\"\n        pattern: \"^ORD-\\\\d+$\"\n        description: \"Order number follows expected format\"\n\n    expected_requests:\n      - method: GET\n        url_pattern: \"/api/orders/*\"\n        response:\n          status: 200\n          body_schema:\n            type: object\n            required:\n              - orderId\n              - status\n              - items\n\nflows:\n  - id: browse-to-checkout\n    description: \"User browses products, adds to cart, and completes checkout\"\n    steps:\n      - navigate: /products\n        description: \"Start at product listing\"\n\n      - assert_page: product-list\n\n      - action: click\n        selector: \".product-card:first-child .add-to-cart\"\n        description: \"Add first product to cart\"\n\n      - action: wait_for_request\n        url_pattern: \"/api/cart/items\"\n        method: POST\n        description: \"Add-to-cart API call completes\"\n\n      - action: assert_visible\n        selector: \".cart-badge\"\n        description: \"Cart badge shows item count\"\n\n      - navigate: /cart\n        description: \"Go to cart page\"\n\n      - assert_page: cart\n\n      - action: click\n        selector: \"[data-testid=checkout-button]\"\n        description: \"Proceed to checkout\"\n\n      - action: wait_for_navigation\n        url_pattern: \"/checkout\"\n\n      - assert_page: checkout\n\n      - action: fill\n        selector: \"#card-number\"\n        value: \"4111111111111111\"\n      - action: fill\n        selector: \"#card-expiry\"\n        value: \"12/28\"\n      - action: fill\n        selector: \"#card-cvc\"\n        value: \"123\"\n\n      - action: click\n        selector: \"button.place-order\"\n        description: \"Place the order\"\n\n      - action: wait_for_request\n        url_pattern: \"/api/orders\"\n        method: POST\n        description: \"Order creation API call\"\n\n      - action: wait_for_navigation\n        url_pattern: \"/order/confirmation*\"\n\n      - assert_page: confirmation\n\nhooks:\n  setup:\n    - name: \"Create test user\"\n      type: api_call\n      method: POST\n      url: \"{{base_url}}/api/test/users\"\n      body:\n        email: \"test@example.com\"\n        password: \"test123\"\n      save_as: test_user\n\n    - name: \"Seed product catalog\"\n      type: api_call\n      method: POST\n      url: \"{{base_url}}/api/test/seed-products\"\n      body:\n        count: 10\n\n  teardown:\n    - name: \"Delete test user\"\n      type: api_call\n      method: DELETE\n      url: \"{{base_url}}/api/test/users/{{test_user.id}}\"\n\n    - name: \"Clean up test orders\"\n      type: shell\n      command: \"curl -X DELETE {{base_url}}/api/test/orders?user={{test_user.id}}\"\n\nvariables:\n  base_url: \"${TARGET_BASE_URL}\"\n"
    }
  ],
  "patterns": [
    {
      "name": "Minimal valid spec",
      "description": "The smallest possible valid spec — just version and name",
      "yaml_snippet": "version: \"1.0\"\nname: \"My App Spec\""
    },
    {
      "name": "Page with visual assertions",
      "description": "A page that checks for specific elements and text on screen",
      "yaml_snippet": "pages:\n  - id: login\n    path: /login\n    title: \"Login\"\n    visual_assertions:\n      - type: element_exists\n        selector: \"form#login-form\"\n        description: \"Login form is present\"\n      - type: text_contains\n        selector: \"h1\"\n        text: \"Welcome\"\n      - type: element_count\n        selector: \".nav-item\"\n        min: 3\n        max: 10"
    },
    {
      "name": "Scenario with interaction steps",
      "description": "A scenario testing a user workflow on a page",
      "yaml_snippet": "scenarios:\n  - id: submit-form\n    description: \"User fills and submits the form\"\n    steps:\n      - action: fill\n        selector: \"#email\"\n        value: \"user@example.com\"\n      - action: fill\n        selector: \"#password\"\n        value: \"secret123\"\n      - action: click\n        selector: \"button[type=submit]\"\n      - action: wait_for_navigation\n        url_pattern: \"/dashboard\"\n      - action: assert_visible\n        selector: \".welcome-message\""
    },
    {
      "name": "API request assertions",
      "description": "Assert that a page makes specific API calls with expected response shapes",
      "yaml_snippet": "expected_requests:\n  - method: GET\n    url_pattern: \"/api/users\"\n    description: \"Fetches user list\"\n    response:\n      status: 200\n      content_type: \"application/json\"\n      body_schema:\n        type: object\n        required: [items, total]\n        properties:\n          items:\n            type: array\n          total:\n            type: number"
    },
    {
      "name": "Multi-page flow",
      "description": "A flow that navigates across multiple pages with assertions at each step",
      "yaml_snippet": "flows:\n  - id: checkout-flow\n    description: \"User completes a purchase\"\n    steps:\n      - navigate: /products\n      - assert_page: product-list\n      - action: click\n        selector: \".add-to-cart\"\n      - navigate: /cart\n      - assert_page: cart\n      - action: click\n        selector: \"#checkout\"\n      - action: wait_for_navigation\n        url_pattern: \"/checkout\"\n      - assert_page: checkout"
    },
    {
      "name": "Setup and teardown hooks",
      "description": "Hooks to create/clean test data before and after verification",
      "yaml_snippet": "hooks:\n  setup:\n    - name: \"Create test user\"\n      type: api_call\n      method: POST\n      url: \"{{base_url}}/api/test/users\"\n      body:\n        email: \"test@example.com\"\n      save_as: test_user\n    - name: \"Reset database\"\n      type: shell\n      command: \"npm run db:seed\"\n  teardown:\n    - name: \"Delete test user\"\n      type: api_call\n      method: DELETE\n      url: \"{{base_url}}/api/test/users/{{test_user.id}}\""
    },
    {
      "name": "CLI verification",
      "description": "Spec for validating a CLI tool's output, exit codes, and behavior",
      "yaml_snippet": "cli:\n  binary: \"node dist/cli.js\"\n  timeout_ms: 10000\n  commands:\n    - id: help\n      description: \"Help flag shows usage\"\n      args: [\"--help\"]\n      expected_exit_code: 0\n      stderr_assertions:\n        - type: text_contains\n          text: \"Usage:\"\n    - id: version\n      args: [\"--version\"]\n      expected_exit_code: 0\n      stdout_assertions:\n        - type: text_matches\n          pattern: \"^\\\\d+\\\\.\\\\d+\\\\.\\\\d+$\"\n    - id: invalid-input\n      args: [\"--nonexistent\"]\n      expected_exit_code: 1\n      stderr_assertions:\n        - type: text_contains\n          text: \"Unknown option\""
    },
    {
      "name": "Defaults and assumptions",
      "description": "Global properties and preconditions for the spec",
      "yaml_snippet": "defaults:\n  no_5xx: true\n  no_console_errors: true\n  no_uncaught_exceptions: true\n  page_load_timeout_ms: 5000\n\nassumptions:\n  - type: url_reachable\n    url: \"{{base_url}}\"\n    description: \"Application is running\"\n  - type: env_var_set\n    name: \"TEST_API_KEY\"\n    description: \"API key is configured\""
    },
    {
      "name": "Template variables",
      "description": "Dynamic values using template syntax and environment variables",
      "yaml_snippet": "variables:\n  base_url: \"${TARGET_BASE_URL}\"\n  api_key: \"${TEST_API_KEY}\"\n  test_email: \"test@example.com\"\n\n# Use in specs with double braces:\n# {{base_url}}, {{api_key}}, {{test_email}}\n# Hook results: {{test_user.id}} (from save_as: test_user)"
    }
  ],
  "assertion_types": {
    "visual_assertions": [
      "element_exists — Check that a CSS selector matches an element in the DOM",
      "text_contains — Check that an element's text includes a substring",
      "text_matches — Check that an element's text matches a regex pattern",
      "screenshot_region — Visual regression check on a page region",
      "element_count — Check the count of elements matching a selector (min/max)"
    ],
    "scenario_step_actions": [
      "click — Click an element (requires selector)",
      "fill — Type text into an input (requires selector + value)",
      "select — Choose a dropdown option (requires selector + value)",
      "hover — Hover over an element (requires selector)",
      "wait_for_request — Wait for a network request (requires url_pattern, optional method)",
      "wait_for_navigation — Wait for page navigation (requires url_pattern)",
      "assert_visible — Assert an element is visible (requires selector)",
      "assert_text — Assert element contains text (requires selector + text)",
      "assert_not_visible — Assert an element is NOT visible (requires selector)",
      "keypress — Press a key (requires key, e.g. \"Enter\", \"Control+A\")",
      "scroll — Scroll to element or position (optional selector or direction: top/bottom)",
      "wait — Wait for a duration in ms (requires duration)"
    ],
    "cli_output_assertions": [
      "text_contains — Output contains a substring",
      "text_matches — Output matches a regex pattern",
      "json_schema — Output is valid JSON matching a JSON Schema",
      "json_path — A specific JSON path has an expected value",
      "empty — Output is empty",
      "line_count — Output has a specific number of lines (min/max)"
    ],
    "flow_step_types": [
      "navigate — Navigate to a URL path",
      "assert_page — Assert current page matches a PageSpec by id",
      "action — Perform an interactive action (same types as scenario steps)"
    ],
    "hook_types": [
      "api_call — Make an HTTP request (method, url, headers, body, save_as)",
      "shell — Run a shell command (command, save_as)"
    ],
    "assumption_types": [
      "url_reachable — A URL responds with 2xx to a HEAD request",
      "env_var_set — An environment variable is set and non-empty",
      "api_returns — An API endpoint returns an expected status code",
      "selector_exists — A CSS selector exists on a given page"
    ]
  },
  "template_variables": {
    "syntax": "{{variable_name}} for spec variables, ${ENV_VAR} for environment variables",
    "description": "Variables defined in the \"variables\" section can be referenced anywhere in the spec using {{name}}. Environment variables use ${NAME} syntax. Hook steps with \"save_as\" create variables accessible as {{saved_name.field}}."
  },
  "tips": [
    "Start with the minimal spec (version + name) and build up incrementally.",
    "Use \"specify spec lint\" to validate structure before running against a live app.",
    "Every page should have at least one visual assertion — otherwise there's nothing to verify.",
    "Scenarios should end with an assertion step (assert_visible, assert_text) to verify the outcome.",
    "Use descriptive IDs that read like sentences: \"login\", \"successful-checkout\", \"filter-by-date\".",
    "Use the \"description\" field liberally — it helps both humans and LLMs understand intent.",
    "Set defaults (no_5xx, no_console_errors) to catch common regressions across all pages.",
    "Add assumptions to prevent false failures (e.g., assert the target URL is reachable first).",
    "For CLI specs, test both happy paths (exit 0) and error paths (non-zero exit codes).",
    "Use json_path assertions to check specific JSON output values without validating the entire structure.",
    "Template variables keep specs portable — use ${ENV_VAR} for environment-specific values.",
    "Flows connect pages into user journeys — use assert_page to verify you landed on the right page.",
    "The \"quantifier\" field (always/sometimes) marks whether an assertion must hold on every run or just some.",
    "The \"confidence\" field (observed/inferred/reviewed) tracks how an assertion was established."
  ]
}

{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Specify Spec",
  "description": "Computational spec format for functional verification of web applications.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "version",
    "name"
  ],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "version": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Spec format version."
    },
    "name": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Human-readable name for this spec."
    },
    "description": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional description of what this spec covers."
    },
    "pages": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/PageSpec"
      }
    },
    "flows": {
